&lt;p&gt;Fender Musical Instruments Corporation es una marca mundialmente famosa con oficinas en todo el mundo. Fender nació en el sur de California y ha construido una influencia mundial que va más allá del estudio y el escenario. Un Fender es más que un instrumento; es un símbolo cultural que resuena globalmente.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Estamos buscando un&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Auditor de Calidad&lt;/strong&gt; para unirse a nuestro equipo, en Ensenada, México. Esta posición se encarga de garantizar que las piezas y los productos producidos en Fender. En esta función, será responsable de garantizar que las piezas y productos producidos en Fender Ensenada cumplan con todas las expectativas del cliente; Experto en calidad y posición práctica que actúa rápida y eficazmente cuando se encuentran no conformidades. Mantiene la interpretación más reciente de los requisitos del sistema de calidad y, por lo tanto, asegura de que las prácticas documentadas cumplan con la verdadera interpretación de los estándares del sistema de gestión de la calidad.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Funciones Esenciales:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Asegurar que las piezas y productos producidos en Fender Ensenada cumplan con todas las expectativas del cliente; Experto en calidad y posición práctica que actúa rápida y eficazmente cuando se encuentran no conformidades. Mantiene la interpretación más reciente de los requisitos del sistema de calidad y, por lo tanto, se asegura de que las prácticas documentadas cumplan con la verdadera interpretación de los estándares del sistema de gestión de la calidad.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsabilidades clave:&lt;/strong&gt;·&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Colaborar con el equipo de Manufactura, Ingeniería, y Calidad para garantizar las características críticas del producto.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluar los requerimientos y especificaciones de los procesos para garantizar que se sigan de la forma en la que están descritos.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Realizar inspecciones dimensionales, estéticas y funcionales a los materiales en proceso y productos terminados.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participar en investigación de defectos, ejercicios de solución de problemas y evaluación de modos de fallas.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ejecutar planes de inspección para componentes, subconjuntos y montajes finales.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generar reportes de auditoría e inspección que ayuden a determinar oportunidades de mejora en los procesos.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dar seguimiento a hallazgos de inspección y auditoría para asegurar el cierre de las acciones correctivas.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requerimientos:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conocimiento en los procesos de fabricación de cuellos, cuerpos y/o guitarras.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1 año de experiencia en inspección con experiencia en carpintería o fabricación electrónica&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Diploma de escuela secundaria o certificado de preparatoria.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manejo de Office, las aplicaciones de SAP.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excelente comunicación verbal y escrita.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interpretación de dibujos&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Habilidades para resolver problemas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conocimientos y manejo de instrumentos de medición (vernier, medidor de profundidad, pin gages, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Acerca de los instrumentos musicales Fender:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fender Musical Instruments Corporation (FMIC) es uno de los principales fabricantes, comercializadores y distribuidores de instrumentos musicales del mundo. Su cartera de marcas incluye Fender®, Squier®, Presonus®, Gretsch®, Jackson®, EVH®, Charvel®, Bigsby® y Groove Tubes®, entre otras. Para más información, visite www.fe

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fender Musical Instruments Corporation &lt;/strong&gt;is a world-famous brand with offices across the globe&lt;strong&gt;. &lt;/strong&gt;Fender was born in Southern California and has built a worldwide influence beyond the studio and the stage. A Fender is more than an instrument; it’s a cultural symbol that resonates globally.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are searching for a Business Application Analyst II - Master Data to join our team in Ensenada, Mexico&lt;strong&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt; The role is a member of the FMIC Information Technology department, supporting the SAP material master system. This position will include all the responsibilities of the Business Application Analyst I – Master Data, with additional responsibilities, including a specific focus on developing basic Winshuttle Studio transaction and query scripts and extended outreach to FMIC colleagues for support. The person in this position will take an active role as the point of contact and delegator of data governance initiatives established by management for the Master Data Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Functions:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assists in deploying data governance rules at the behest of upper management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reconcile discrepancies to maintain information quality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Initiates and maintains communication with company stakeholders to ensure that quality assurance standards are met.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provides basic training for new Master Data Team members.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Training of all SAP users who consume or contribute master data information.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Documentation of all Master Data processes and data governance directives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Annual “Lunch and Learn” presentation of Master Data initiatives or systems operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organize and delegate daily requests from internal customers to update/correct material master, purchasing info records, source lists, BOMS, and sales status.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic development of Winshuttle Studio Scripts, including queries.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creation of best practice workflow for data processes and procedures, working directly with the Master Data Team lead in implementation.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Development of audit reports using Winshuttle query or SE16&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify manual processes and optimize them with fully or semi-automated processes.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and maintain communication with all functional users and stakeholders to support and derive improvements based on user experience.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintenance of QM inspection setups in SAP&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Additional duties as assigned&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3 to 5 years of experience with ERP, specifically material master, is preferred (SAP) – data consolidation and workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior experience with relational databases and MDM best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-motivated learner with strong analytical and critical thinking skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A drive to learn new skills and technologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Possess and demonstrate advanced knowledge of Microsoft Excel.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;SQL and Python knowledge is preferred but not necessary.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of all FMIC-branded product lines to satisfy quality assurance goals and responsibilities is preferred but not required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extensive use of project management tools like JIRA or Trello.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Professional English proficiency, with strong verbal and written communication skills, is required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Fender Musical Instruments:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fender Musical Instruments Corporation (FMIC) is

&lt;p&gt;As the world&#39;s leading guitar manufacturer, Fender Musical Instruments Corporation &quot;FMIC&quot; has become synonymous with all things rock &#39;n&#39; roll. Our iconic instruments such as the Telecaster, Stratocaster, Precision Bass &amp;amp; Jazz Bass guitars are known worldwide as the instruments that started the rock revolution and they continue to be highly prized by today.&amp;nbsp; Today, FMIC brands include Fender®, Squier®, Gretsch®, Jackson®, Charvel® and EVH® among others. With an illustrious history dating back to 1946, Fender has touched and transformed music worldwide and in nearly every genre: rock ‘n’ roll, country and western, jazz, rhythm and blues and many others. Everyone from beginners and hobbyists to the world’s most acclaimed artists and performers have used Fender instruments and amps, in the process making the company not only a revered music industry name, but also a cultural icon.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is our vision to continue championing THE SPIRIT OF ROCK-N-ROLL throughout the world and our mission is to support every player at every stage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Business Development Manager &lt;/strong&gt;will primarily be responsible for selling specific Fender Brands product lines into allocated sales areas whilst maintaining effective account management for all customers. They will be expected to be a product evangelist with a keen eye for detail, using data to recognise opportunities for commercial achievement. The Business Development Manager will manage the end-to-end relationship between a dealer and the Fender Business, liaising with and owning the relationship and communications to and from all internal departments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Main Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Make regular sales calls to accounts in the assigned area and keep in contact between visits by telephone, zoom and e-mail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strive to achieve budgeted sales targets for the allocated sales area.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and maintain positive working relationships with customers and potential new clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible for all visual merchandising and product representation in-store and online to comply with company requirements and regulations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible via all channels for assisting the development of product knowledge and training to retail account staff on Company brands using Academy and in store visits.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain control of dealers’ stock and open orders, ensuring correct stock levels are maintained, new products are presented and exit strategies for discontinued products implemented.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and assist dealer accounts on promotions and rebate schemes, ensuring terms and conditions are adhered to.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a high level of product knowledge for the relevant product lines being sold.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential skills and experience&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience within a sales environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of the Musical Instrument Industry&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in the use of Microsoft Word, Excel, and Outlook.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work on own initiative and be self-motivated.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent interpersonal skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effective communication skills, both written and verbal.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to prioritise work and adapt to changing priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
